#!N 
#!CSeaGreen #!N  #!Rasxgrp Assigning Execution 
Groups to Workstations #!N #!EC #!N #!N Once you have decomposed 
your visual program into execution groups, you can assign these groups 
to workstations (or hosts). If you do not specify a host 
for a particular execution group, the group will be executed on 
the master. Execution groups are assigned to a host using the 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execution Group Assignment... #!EF dialog box (  #!Lpg299,dxall490 f Figure 99  #!EL  ). #!N 
#!N The dialog box consists of three parts: #!N #!I0 #!N 
#!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Groups and Hosts #!EF #!I50 #!N Displays 
the name of an execution group and the host on which 
the group is executed. If a host name is not given, 
then "localhost" is displayed as the host name. #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Host Name #!EF #!I50 #!N A text field for specifying 
the name of a host on which an execution group is 
to be executed. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Pushbuttons #!EF #!I50 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   OK #!EF causes the assignments of executions groups to host 
names and closes the dialog box.  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Options... #!EF opens a 
dialog box that allows you to specify startup options (e.g., memory 
size, or the Data Explorer executive that will be started on 
the host. #!I0 #!N #!N #!Cbrown #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*    #!Rpg299 #!N Graphics 
omitted from Online Documentation. Please see the manual. #!N #!N Figure 
99. Execution Group Assignment Dialog Box #!EF #!N #!EC #!N #!N 
To assign an execution group to a workstation: #!N #!I0 #!N 
 #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 1. Open the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execution Group 
Assignment... #!EF dialog box by selecting the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Connection #!EF menu 
 #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Execution Group Assignment... #!EF option in either the Visual Program 
Editor or Image Window. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. Select the execution 
group that you wish to assign to a host by clicking 
on its name. #!N #!I30 #!N 3. Enter the host name 
in the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Host Name #!EF text field and hit Enter. 
#!N #!I30 #!N 4. Click on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Options... #!EF button 
to specify any options for the host, for example memory size. 
#!N #!I30 #!N 5. If there are more groups to assign 
to hosts repeat Steps 2 through 4, otherwise, click on  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
OK #!EF . #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N #!N 
